description:
M57 spectra.
Upper left  :Autoguider enhanced image (SDSS colored)
Upper right : Part of the ring nebula used for this spectra 
Lower part : synthetic colored spectra and elements

Nebula high excitation class (He line at 4686 A) : E7 or E8 with E = 2.05
Teff central star = 90 000 to 100 000 K

Ratio S II I(6716)/I(6731) = 1,0645339217
Giving approx up to Ne = 500  / cm3

Te from [N II] procedure gives : 
Te [N II]= 11 500 K

Values for outer ring from 
CHEMICAL ABUNDANCES AND KINEMATICS OF THE RING NEBULA AND ITS HALOS M. A. GUERRERO1 AND A. MANCHADO1- 1997  and Y.-H. CHU
  (http://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1086/304582/meta)
give :

Ne = 615 
Te [N II] = 10240 K

Not so bad for that time..;-)
title: M57 outer ring spectra
